parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the engine RPMs surge
the vehicle won't move
the transmission fails to shift gears
the check engine light and TCS light illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding doors can cause passengers to be trapped inside the vehicle, making it difficult or impossible to exit in an emergency situation, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power sliding doors do not open or close properly
stick shut
or operate intermittently
requiring manual operation or fuse resets.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Bumper Beam Rust and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear bumper beam can cause a loss of rear end crash protection, increasing the risk of injury or accident in a rear-end collision.
symptoms: The rear bumper beam rusts and breaks apart
causing pieces to fall out from under the bumper cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front engine mount can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or injuries due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The front engine mount breaks or wears out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and shards of metal can cause damage to the vehicle's fuel tank and frame, potentially leading to fuel leaks or fires, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Pieces of rusted metal and unknown shards hang from the vehicle between the fuel tank and frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring can cause the tire to puncture, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noises
clunking sounds
grinding
or rattling from the front of the vehicle
especially when turning or driving over bumps. The vehicle may pull to one side
and the steering may become difficult.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Slipping transmission
delayed engagement
hesitation
or complete loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal hesitation can increase the stopping distance, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.
